wikipedia_page.main: Ralph Phillips (9 August 1933 – September 2011) was an English footballer who made 112 appearances in the Football League playing as a full back for Northampton Town and Darlington in the 1950s and 1960s. He began his senior career with Middlesbrough, without representing them in the League.

response: Ralph Phillips is the name of:
*Ralph Phillips (Looney Tunes), a Looney Tunes character
*Ralph Phillips Lowe, former Governor of Iowa
